OL,3,CGuernsey veteran receives Ukrainian
OL,4,Caward for clearing mines
OL,6,FThe Ukrainian government has awarded a
OL,7,Fformer soldier from Guernsey the
OL,8,Fofficial Cross of Support for his
OL,9,Fservices during the war.
OL,11,FBen Remfrey MBE, founder of the
OL,12,Fcharity Friends of Ukraine EOD, has
OL,13,Fbeen helping to clear mines and other
OL,14,Fexplosives in the country.
OL,16,FHis charity has taught around 400
OL,17,FUkrainians how to detonate Russian
OL,18,Fammunitions that land in their country.
OL,20,FIt's thought around 60% of those
OL,21,Fammunitions fail to explode.
